news_header: Record bankruptcy applications in Finland with 128 in one week, highest since 2020s.
news_original_title: Vuoden alussa tehty poikkeuksellisen paljon konkurssihakemuksia
news_text: Finland has seen a surge in bankruptcy applications, with 128 filed in one week, the highest since the 2020s. In 2024, 3006 enterprises went bankrupt, the most in the 2000s, primarily affecting small firms.
